    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1040"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1040">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.8273/43.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister at Mexico
                            City</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. I congratulate Department for my being able at last to secure the release of
                    Vice Consul Silliman who will be delivered to me here <pb facs="0780" n="664"
                        xml:id="pg_664"/> according my demand. Order for his release has just been
                    telegraphed to proper authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
